    "poemName": "Composed upon Mount Isso, March 22, 2022",
    "poemAuthor": "Angelos",
    "poemContent": {
        "type": "fragment",
        "styles": [],
        "children": [
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "One spring lunchtime (led by her),"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "They found a shiny basketball, frozen on the road,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Between the grand fields, it's usual home."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "The wizened earth has never troubled us;"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "No lions chase, or hidden snakes to miss,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Or teachers to comfort them, when the youngsters take the piss;"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Two trunk-less goalposts, and a few dotted trees just stand."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "But this basketball was no ordinary one."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Small gemstones glittered between it's plastic skin,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Melting in that girl's eyes."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "She was an A* student and wondered as she wandered"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "How a sphere can stand still, on the slope of a hill."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Proud of her skill, she knew she could find it,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Those beams of light were nothing but photons."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "A God given gift; perhaps a Trojan horse?"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "This was magic, but it couldn't; be vane."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "She crouched right down above this mystical object,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "And checked her under-eye under he mirror,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "But she was sane."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "As she rose from that stroke of shock,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "She raises her foot right up,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "straight into a perfect right angle to her upright stance,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "And as if with voluntary human instinct,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Booted the magic ball; turned savage."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Still in the stature of her shape, grew the dunnest stinging pain."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "The very basketball, spat out it's grey contents."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "They were bombarded by a hollow ball."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "They huffed and puffed again,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "For so it seemed, with struggle of her own,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Measuring motion like a living thing,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "To haul a crappy plastic ball in the bin!"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Back to the covert of sixth-form centre,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "There hung a darkness, call it solitude."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "No familiar shapes remained;"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "No pleasant images of trees or green fields;"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Four year 11s running away giggling,"
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Day by day, a plague to her dreams."
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            }
        ]
    },
    "pageStyle": "poem-centre",
    "pageBackground": ""
}